Psychotropic drugs can induce weight gain and a metabolic syndrome, reducing the 
quality of life and the life expectancy of patients. Weight gain is also 
responsible for poor adherence to treatment and therefore relapses of mental 
illness. This weight gain and the metabolic syndrome are insufficiently treated 
for obese patients with mental disorders. Recommendations exist.

