In the context of the White Book of Physical and Rehabilitation Medicine (PRM) 
in Europe, this paper deals with the future perspectives of PRM in Europe 
according to the actual vision of the European Bodies. All Chapters stress the 
big changes that Europe is facing in terms of demography, life expectancy, 
survival rates, disability burden, increasing prevalence of long-term health 
conditions, progress in technology, but also health costs and society changes in 
terms of requirements of wellness and quality of life together with health. All 
these challenges combined with the specificities of PRM, that is the medical 
